Time Model Statistics

  • DB Time represents total time in user calls
  • DB CPU represents CPU time of foreground processes
  • Total CPU Time represents foreground and background processes
  • Statistics including the word "background" measure background process time, therefore do not contribute to the DB time statistic
  • Ordered by % of DB time in descending order, followed by Statistic Name

ADDM Task ADDM:2216396004_1_199

          ADDM Report for Task 'ADDM:2216396004_1_199'
          --------------------------------------------

Analysis Period
---------------
AWR snapshot range from 198 to 199.
Time period starts at 24-DEC-23 01.00.37
Time period ends at 24-DEC-23 01.30.38

Analysis Target
---------------
Database 'RMGTIBN' with DB ID 2216396004.
Database version 19.0.0.0.0.
ADDM performed an analysis of instance rmgtibn, numbered 1 and hosted at
RMULBGORA5002.

Activity During the Analysis Period
-----------------------------------
Total database time was 29670 seconds.
The average number of active sessions was 16.47.

Summary of Findings
-------------------
   Description                               Active Sessions      Recommendations
                                             Percent of Activity
   ----------------------------------------  -------------------  ---------------
1  Commits and Rollbacks                     7.41 | 45.01         1
2  "User I/O" wait Class                     4.24 | 25.71         0
3  Top SQL Statements                        4.2 | 25.49          5
4  Top Segments by "User I/O" and "Cluster"  2.79 | 16.95         4


~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


          Findings and Recommendations
          ----------------------------

Finding 1: Commits and Rollbacks
Impact is 7.41 active sessions, 45.01% of total activity.
---------------------------------------------------------
Waits on event "log file sync" while performing COMMIT and ROLLBACK operations
were consuming significant database time.

   Recommendation 1: Host Configuration
   Estimated benefit is 7.41 active sessions, 45.01% of total activity.
   --------------------------------------------------------------------
   Action
      Investigate the possibility of improving the performance of I/O to the
      online redo log files.
   Rationale
      The average size of writes to the online redo log files was 24 K and the
      average time per write was 2 milliseconds.
   Rationale
      The total I/O throughput on redo log files was 15 M per second for reads
      and 30 M per second for writes.
   Rationale
      The redo log I/O throughput was divided as follows: 0% by RMAN and
      recovery, 66% by Log Writer, 0% by Archiver, 0% by Streams AQ and 33% by
      all other activity.

   Symptoms That Led to the Finding:
   ---------------------------------
      Wait class "Commit" was consuming significant database time.
      Impact is 7.41 active sessions, 45.01% of total activity.


Finding 2: "User I/O" wait Class
Impact is 4.23 active sessions, 25.71% of total activity.
---------------------------------------------------------
Wait class "User I/O" was consuming significant database time.
The throughput of the I/O subsystem was not significantly lower than expected.

   No recommendations are available.


Finding 3: Top SQL Statements
Impact is 4.2 active sessions, 25.49% of total activity.

statements offer a good opportunity for performance improvement.
